<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Invites IMF to Have Urgent Talks in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government Monday
invited the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to send a team of
experts to Moscow for urgent talks on the worsening Russian
financial situation.
</P>
<P>
Russian deputy Foreign Minister Georgy Mamedov, who is in
London to brief senior government officials of the Group of Seven
(G7) countries meeting in London, announced the new Russian
government's invitation to the IMF.
</P>
<P>
"We have invited the IMF to come back to Moscow this week for
urgent talks. We have issued an invitation to them and hope they
will come. This is very important for them and for us," Mamedov
said.
</P>
<P>
On the one-day G7 London talks, Mamedov noted that the G7
officials expressed the hope that the government led by new Prime
Minister Yevgeny Primakov would succeed as soon as possible in
stabilizing Russia's economy.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that the London meeting had been "very
successful economically and politically", saying "There was a lot
of enthusiasm for the fact that we have a new prime minister and
that the period of uncertainty is over."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
