<HEADLINE> 7 Booklets to Be Published to Preserve Nigeria's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian Book Foundation
(NBF) is scheduled to publish seven booklets in a bid to preserve
"certain fading aspects" of the nation's culture and traditions,
the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
NAN quoted NBF President Chukwuemka Ike as saying that the
foundation was collecting for publication materials on
rain-making, rights of passage, wine-tapping, traditional
medicine and orthopaedic practice.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that NBF's initiatives would inspire
individuals and groups to do something to preserve the rich
cultural values of the peoples of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Ike, a renowned author in the West African country, disclosed
that a curriculum had been recommended for police colleges to
enable all policemen to recognize and deal with pirated
materials.
</P>
<P>
He announced that his organization would convene a book forum
in Ibadan, western Nigeria, on September 22 aimed at "producing a
charter and striking a new deal to guide relationships between
writers and publishers in Nigeria." 
</P>
</TEXT>
