<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Killing of Iranian Diplomats Condemnable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A senior Iranian diplomat
in Lahore said Monday the killing of Iranian diplomats at the
northern Afghan town of Mazar-i-Sharif allegedly by the Taliban
militia was a condemnable act.
</P>
<P>
Aghai Pirouz Ghofrani, Iranian Consul General in Lahore, made
the remarks while talking to the mourners at a condolence meeting
held at his residence.
</P>
<P>
"Whatever the Talibans did in Mazar-i-Sharif did not reflect a
fair play," he was quoted by the Associated Press of Pakistan
(APP) as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Consul General hoped that the relations between
Pakistan and Iran would continue to strengthen despite certain
developments in the region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another APP report said that the Taliban militia
has rejected the Iranian demand to hand over the suspects in the
killing of nine Iranian diplomats to Iran, saying "it will not
turn over any suspect in the killings."
</P>
<P>
A Taliban official has called the killing as "an internal
matter", and said one of the suspects who is arrested will be
tried in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The nine Iranian diplomats were killed when the Taliban forces
stormed into the northern Afghan town of Mazar-i-Sharif early last
month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
