<HEADLINE> 7 Dead Iranian Diplomats Identified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The bodies of seven Iranians
killed by Afghan Taliban militia have been identified by the
International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC), the Iranian
official news agency IRNA reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
It said that an ICRC team has left Afghanistan for Tehran
after identifying the bodies with assistance from an Iranian
technical team.
</P>
<P>
The ICRC team was dispatched to Afghanistan to identify and
transfer the bodies of the Iranian diplomats and IRNA reporter
killed on August 8 in Mazari Sharif when the Taliban took over
the city.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Mohsen Aminzadeh on Monday
told a group of foreign diplomats that eight Iranian diplomats
and an IRNA correspondent were killed by the Taliban, a diplomat
source told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that 11 Iranian diplomats and an IRNA
reporter were present in the Iranian consulate in Mazari
Sharif. However, Aminzadeh put the figure of Iranian diplomats at
10, two of them escaped the massacre.
</P>
<P>
One diplomat was not in the consulate at the time of the
massacre, he said, another was wounded but he successfully fled
from the scene.
</P>
<P>
Media reports said that the bodies of the killed Iranians
would be flown to Tehran around 2300 local times Monday
night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
