<HEADLINE> Romania Wishes Russia to Pursue Stabilization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister
Radu Vasile Monday expressed his hope that Russia would be able to
pursue its stabilization and reform process.
</P>
<P>
According to the national Rompres news agency, Radu Vasile had
a meeting on Monday with Russian Ambassador to Bucharest Valeri
Keneaikin at the Victoria government Palace.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Valeri Keneaikin conveyed to Radu Vasile
the message of his Russian counterpart Yevgeni Primakov,
expressing the latter's appreciation for the Romanian government's
"realistic and tempered attitude" and renewing the invitation for
Romanian Prime Minister to visit Russia" as soon as possible."
</P>
<P>
Valeri Keneaikin stressed the need for the two countries to
boost their economic ties, saying that the bilateral relationships
were below the two countries' economic potential.
</P>
<P>
There were a full range of Romanian products that had been
"appreciated and expected" on the Russian market, such as
furniture, ready-made clothes, wine, cars, the ambassador added,
expressing his confidence that the Romanian export to Russia could
be reinvigorated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
