<HEADLINE> S. African Diplomat Freed in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's Supreme Court
Monday released conditionally Robert Mcbride, former Director in
charge of Asia and Middle East desk in South Africa's Foreign
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
He has been put into Machava prison near Maputo after he was
suspected of being involved in illegal arms smuggling and
espionage on March 9.
</P>
<P>
As his case is now under investigation, Mcbride is set free on
the condition he will come to answer questions at court the
minute he is informed.
</P>
<P>
Setting free along with Mcbride at the same time were six
South Africans who had been imprisoned for the same reason. And
their lawyer Jose de Nascimento had expressed satisfaction with
the court's decision at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Mcbride and his party will leave for South Africa Monday, the
Mocambique Information Agency reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
