<HEADLINE> Blair Pledges not to Distance from Embattled Clinton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 14 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair made clear Monday that he would not distance himself from
U.S. President Bill Clinton who is being plagued by sex scandals.
</P>
<P>
A Dowing Street spokesman was quoted by Reuters as saying
Monday "The Prime Minister (Blair) is not a fair-weather friend"
and Blair would hold a scheduled meeting with Clinton in New York
next week.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said: "The Prime Minister doesn't dump people
just because some report goes on the Internet."
</P>
<P>
