<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Government, Central Bank to Talk with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Russia has set up a commission
to coordinate talks over the restructuring Russian banks' debts to
foreign creditors, the Itar-Tass news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to a joint press release of the Finance Ministry and
the Central Bank, the commission, consisting of officials from the
two government bodies, will assist the talks on deals made before
August 17, when the government of Sergei Kiriyenko announced a
moratorium on repayment of some foreign debts.
</P>
<P>
A negotiating committee representing foreign creditors will
soon be set up, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
Moscow has asked all creditors to refrain from legal actions
before the negotiations yield mutually acceptable results, the
press release said.
</P>
<P>
Under a government decree issued on September 10, a delegation
will be formed for talks with foreign creditors. The delegation is
to be headed by Deputy Finance Minister Mikhail Kasyanov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980915.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgium Issues Flood Warning, Starts Evacuation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Belgium issued on Monday a
third-degree flood warning and started evacuating people from the
country's northeastern part menaced by swollen rivers.
</P>
<P>
Belgian State Security Secretary Jan Peeters told a press
conference that the flood warning was issued to evacuate people
from nine communities in provinces of Brahant, Limbourg and Liege,
where continuous rains caused the water in rivers to rise sharply.
</P>
<P>
The rivers concerned include the Ambleve, the Vesdre, the
Hoegne and the Demer.
</P>
<P>
The water level in the rivers has already surpassed the ones
that caused the 1993 and 1995 flooding in the same region, the
state security secretary warned.
</P>
<P>
The situation in communities of Chaudfontaine and Esneux were
especially dangerous and machines for making sand bags had to be
ferried in from other places.
</P>
<P>
The province of Liege, the country's easternmost province
bordering Germany, is expected to encounter a worse situation in
the coming days in that the country's largest river Meuse runs
through it before entering the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The Meuse also carries excess rain waters with it from France
to Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Third-degree warnings are given in case of catastrophe by
Belgium's provincial authorities that are thus entitled to demand
military assistance if need arises.
</P>
<P>
Continuous rains, that started late last month and kept on and
off for most of the past fortnight, were attributed to the
unusually warmer waters in the North Sea this Summer.
</P>
<P>
When currents of cold-air masses run into hot-air masses rising
above the North Sea they combine and produce rainfalls in nearby
regions.
</P>
<P>
Belgium is now right under the influence of such a
meteorological build-up, said meteorologist Luc de Bontridder.
</P>
<P>
Local weather forecast predicted more rains for this week.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
