<HEADLINE> UNDP Head to Leave in June Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The head of the U.N.
Development Program (UNDP), James Gustave Speth, announced on
Monday that he would leave the agency at the end of June 1999.
</P>
<P>
Speth, an American, becamed the head of the UNDP in June 1993.
</P>
<P>
After the announcement, the European Union, which has been
pushing to take over the U.N. agency, immediately made a bid for
the post.
</P>
<P>
The union sees it as a good chance for the post, given
Washington's declining contributions to the UNDP and the strong
financial backing for it from European countries, including
Sweden, Denmark, Finland.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1965, the UNDP is the United Nations' largest source
of grant assistance for development. It operates in 134 countries.
</P>
