in a new step towards normalizing relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here said that the Egyptian-Sudanese
rapprochement resulted from a joint Syrian-Saudi mediation during
the recent Non-aligned summit in South Africa where the Sudanese
delegation was led by President Omar Al-Bashir and Foreign
Minister Mustafa Othman.
</P>
<P>
The meeting between the foreign ministers of Egypt and
Sudan is expected to discuss a new political accord on improving
the relations between Cairo and Khartoum in a prelude to raising
the level of diplomatic representation, reappointing a new
Egyptian ambassador to Sudan and reopening the various Egyptian
consulates there. 
