<HEADLINE> Writethru: Passenger Plane Hijacked in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A passenger plane of the
Turkish Airlines was hijacked Monday by two gunmen.
</P>
<P>
They hijacked the Airbus 310 type "Seyhan" plane on the
Ankara-Istanbul flight soon after the plane took off from the
Ankara Esenboga Airport.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported that a pilot
of the hijacked plane told the tower in the airport that the
aircraft was hijacked at 20:37 local time (17:37 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Later, the hijacked plane carrying 76 passengers and crew
members landed on the airport in Trabzon province along the Black
Sea of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
A Turkish source told Xinhua that there are three Turkish
Cabinet ministers among the hijacked passengers on board.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the doors of the hijacked plane
were opened and the passengers began to be set free.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has formed a "crisis table" at Ataturk Airport in
Istanbul in a bid to deal with the incident.
</P>
<P>
On February 24 this year, a hijacker hijacked RJ-100 type
passenger plane in Adana, southern Turkey and later landed in
Diyarbakir Airport in southeastern Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
