<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A senior Turkish official
said Monday night that an armed hijacker of a Turkish passenger
plane surrendered at the airport in Trabzon province along the
Black Sea of Turkey after releasing all people on board.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency quoted General Director
of the Turkish Airlines Yusuf Bolayirli that there is no any
high-ranking official among the 76 hijacked passengers and eight
crew.
</P>
