<HEADLINE> Hungary to Strengthen Ties With Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Hungary and Peru have agreed
to carry on regular high-ranking political discussions to improve
trade ties.
</P>
<P>
The accord was reached on Tuesday morning by Hungarian Foreign
Minister Martonyi Janos and his Peruvian counterpart Eduardo
Costa, who was accompanying Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori on
his visit here.
</P>
<P>
Hungary was trying to expand its relations with those countries
enjoying steady economic development and stable political
situations including Peru, said Hungarian Foreign Ministry
spokesman Horvath Gabor.
</P>
<P>
Both countries agreed it is important to tap the potential
between them in trade, he said.
</P>
<P>
Peru is Hungary's fourth biggest trading partner in Latin
America. Trade between the two countries reached 26 million
U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also expressed Hungary's intention to hold
inclusive consultations with Peru on global issues. 
</P>
