<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam, U.S. Start Sixth Round of Trade Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and the United States
began their sixth round of talks on a bilateral trade agreement in
Hanoi on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will deal with issues involving the rights of
American firms to engage in import and export activities in
Vietnam and the degree of openness in the service market, sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam Trade Ministry officials said Vietnam must revise a
number of trade policies that were inconsistent with World Trade
Organization (WTO) principles if it wanted to solve the problems
in those issues.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam had yet to discuss tax issues and the U.S. was concerned
about how much Vietnam would open its market to American products,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
A U.S. diplomat said this round of talks was expected to last
till next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The main contents of the Vietnam-U.S. trade pact were basically
the same as an agreement Vietnam will sign with WTO, but the
U.S. demands a number of higher standards for services, investment
and intellectual property, a Vietnam's official newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said because of the two countries' different
levels of development, and different legal systems and economic
management, it would take several more rounds of talks to discuss
the pact. 
</P>
</TEXT>
