<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh, Canada Sign MOU on Food Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and Canada Tuesday
signed a memorandum of understanding (MOU) under which Canada will
provide wheat worth 24.29 million U.S. dollars over a three-year
period beginning this year, the official BSS news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Through its food assistance, Canada will lend support to the
vulnerable group development and rural development programs being
implemented in the country, including those for the Chittagong
Hill Tracts, the rural maintenance program, and the national
nutrition program.
</P>
<P>
The MOU also covers the 16.49 million dollars in emergency food
aid recently announced in support of food relief.
</P>
<P>
A memorandum of understanding on 3.27 million dollars for a
poultry development project was also signed by the Bangladeshi
government and the Canadian International Development Agency.
</P>
<P>
The project will focus on improving the quality of prepared
poultry feeds to help increase poultry and egg production in
Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The project's objectives will be achieved through the provision
of technical assistance for training, extension services,
demonstrations, contracted services and establishing linkages with
the Canadian poultry sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
