<HEADLINE> Meat-Processing Group to Issue A Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Shuanghui Group from
central China's Henan Province will list 50 million A Shares on
the Shenzhen Stock Exchange on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The group, which operates China's largest base for meat
processing and exports, has a 10-year history and will the first
venture in its sector to list shares.
</P>
<P>
The group plans to raise more than 300 million yuan (36 million
US dollars) from the issue to install new production lines and
established a base to supply 500,000 piglets annually and a fodder
plant with an annual fodder production capacity of 28,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The group recorded 1997 pretax profits of 274 million yuan (33
million US dollars) and a foreign trade volume of more than 100
million US dollars. Shuanghui Group enjoys a broad domestic market
and exports products to more than 20 countries and regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
