<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Market Loses 5.04 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday lost 5.04 points to
3162.18 as against Monday's close of 3167.22.
</P>
<P>
The national index also lost 2.53 points to 1397.57 from
previous close of 1400.10.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted lower at 321.47
and 125.90 compared with previous close of 322.21 and 126.25
respectively.
</P>
<P>
A modest downward reaction in the index heavyweights and a few
others resulted in fractional fall in the sensitive index on BSE
market Tuesday as operators preferred to square up positions.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that with the sensitive index well above the
3110-resistance level, the rally might push it to the next
resistance of 3215 and a modest correction is not ruled out.
</P>
