<HEADLINE> U.N. Asked to Recognize UNITA Breakaway Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Eduardo dos
Santos has asked the United Nations Security Council to recognize
the breakaway "UNITA Renovation Committee" as "the only lawful
dialogist" in the peace process in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a message to the U.N. General Assembly dated September 10
and publicized here Tuesday, Dos Santos said that the Angolan
government has decided to recognize the legality of the "UNITA
Renovation Committee" and at the same time to abandon its
cooperation with Jonas Savimbi, President of the National Union
for Total Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The "UNITA Renovation Committee" is a breakaway from the
UNITA. The group led by the suspended Minister of Hotel and
Tourism Jorge Valentim and other UNITA members in the Angolan
government called on the opposition movement to hold on the peace
process and dismiss Savimbi as the UNITA president.
</P>
<P>
In his message, the Angolan president also asked the U.N. to
withdraw its recognition of Savimbi, stressing that what the
UNITA leader has done demonstrates that "he has put himself as
outlaw and thus is disqualified as the only lawful dialogist in
the Angolan peace process."
</P>
<P>
At the summit of the Southern African Development Community
(SADC) in Grande Baie of north Mauritius, the heads of state and
government had in one voice condemned the war crimes committed by
Savimbi and recognized the status of the "UNITA Renovation
Committee" as the only lawful dialogist in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
They issued a statement saying that what Savimbi has done
proves that he can no longer lead the UNITA in the peace efforts.
</P>
<P>
The statement called upon the U.N., the observers from the
United States, Russia and Portugal and the international
community to recognize the new leadership of the UNITA and
encourage it to cooperate with the government comprehensively in
a bid to accomplish the pending tasks written in the 1994 Lusaka
Peace Protocol. 
</P>
</TEXT>
