<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mafia Boss Arrested in Palermo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Mafia boss Mariano Troia was
arrested Tuesday morning in Palermo, capital of Sicily, Italian
police said.
</P>
<P>
Troia, 65, was among the 30 most wanted criminals in Italy. He
was wanted for several mob slayings including that of leading
Sicilian politician Salvo Lima in 1992.
</P>
<P>
He was unarmed when arrested. Police said he appeared
"resigned" and had put on so much weight that he "looked
completely different form the photo we've been hunting him with".
</P>
<P>
An anti-Mafia prosecutor said Troia had been hiding out in
South Africa until about a year ago when he was summoned back to
try to heal a major rift inside the Cosa Nostra.
</P>
<P>
Troia's standing had risen sharply as a result of the thinning
of the Mafia's top ranks due to recent arrests, and mobsters were
counting on his charisma to restore cohesion, the prosecutor said.
</P>
<P>
Italian police have scored a succession of headline-grabbing
Mafia arrests since 1993, most notably Giovanni Brushca in 1996
and Pietro Aglieri in June 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
