<HEADLINE> First Japanese Trade Fair in Kuwait Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A Japanese trade
exhibition, the first in Kuwait, opened Tuesday in the Kuwaiti
International Trade Fair Center.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, which is sponsored by Kuwait's Ministry of
Commerce and Industry and the Japanese Embassy in Kuwait, will
last till September 21.
</P>
<P>
A huge variety of products made in Japan are exhibited,
namely Japanese cars and car parts, sports and marine
equipment, electric compliance, and computers and accessories.
</P>
<P>
Garments and textiles, perfumes and cosmetics, as well as
foods are also put on show.
</P>
<P>
Assistant Director of the Marketing and Public Relation of
Kuwait's International Fair Company, Basmah Al-Dhaim said "the
aim of hosting the exhibition is to further cement trade
relations between Kuwait and Japan."
</P>
<P>
Japan is considered one of Kuwait's most important trade
partner and a main importer of Kuwait's oil. Japan's imports
from Kuwait last year stood at 3.71 billion U.S. dollars,
while exports of Japanese goods to Kuwait were 949 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In October, Kuwait will hold its "First Week in Japan" in
Japan, which Kuwait's official said will come within the
framework of boosting political and trade relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's First Week in Japan will include an exhibition
displaying Kuwaiti goods as well as seminars and lectures
on administrative and investments issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
