<HEADLINE> DPRK Condemns Japan's Reaction on Its Satellite Launch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) on Tuesday criticized Japan's "concerns"
over the DPRK'S launch of an artificial satellite, said the Korean
Central News Agency (KCNA).
</P>
<P>
The DPRK would suspend negotiations with Japan on bilateral
diplomatic relations until Japan stopped its anti-DPRK acts, said
a spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Japan still regarded the satellite launch as a ballistic
missile launch and attempted to bring the issue to the UN Security
Council and impose "international pressure" upon the DPRK, the
spokesman said. 
