<HEADLINE> Soeharto to be Examined on Savings Accounts Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian former president
Soeharto will be examined in one or two days' time or within this
week at the latest in connection with his claim that he has no
savings accounts abroad.
</P>
<P>
"We will check whether he is indeed as clean as he has claimed
to be and President Habibie has agreed to do it," Supreme Advisory
Council Chairman Baramuli told reporters after a consultation
meeting with Habibie here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said Soeharto would be examined by a special team which had
already been set up by the head of state.
</P>
<P>
"So it is not true that President Habibie is hesitant about
examining former president Soeharto," Baramuli said.
</P>
<P>
In a speech on the channel controlled by his eldest daughter
Siti Hardijanti Rukmana on Sunday, Soeharto said: "The fact is, I
don't have even one cent of savings abroad, don't have accounts at
foreign banks.. let alone hundreds of billion of dollars."
</P>
<P>
American magazine Forbes estimated in July that Soeharto, who
stepped down amid mounting public pressure on May 21, had a
fortune worth 4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Baramuli said the government would also examine Soeharto's
family members as well as his cronies "including those involved in
corruption, collusion and nepotism."
</P>
<P>
He said President Habibie had stated he would build a clean,
respected and corruption-collusion-nepotism-free government.
</P>
<P>
"The Supreme Advisory Council has conveyed its stand to
President Habibie about the need to build a clean and respected
government", Baramuli said.
</P>
<P>
Among those to examine the former president would be the
Attorney General and the Chief of the State Police, Baramuli said,
adding that based on the results of the examination further
actions would be taken.
</P>
<P>
"If he is found guilty, he will be brought to court," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
