<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Health Minister Resigns Over Corruption Scandal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Thai Public Health Minister
Rakkiat Sukthana resigned Tuesday under mounting pressure from the
public over a corruption scandal, the Thai Cabinet announced at
its weekly meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Public Health Ministry is alleged to have pressured
hospitals to buy drugs and medical supplies from specified firms
at inflated prices.
</P>
<P>
The wife of the minister is also charged of having received an
18-million-baht (450,000 U.S. dollar) kick-back from
pharmaceutical distributors.
</P>
<P>
A team consisting of members from the Public Health Ministry
Committee, a House health sub-committee and the Counter Corruption
Commission has been set up to investigate the scandal.
</P>
<P>
However, the result of the investigation is yet to be released.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai said after the cabinet meeting
that the investigation will not stop at Rakkiat's resignation.
</P>
<P>
The resignation of Rakkiat, deputy leader of the coalition
partner Social Action Party, is believed to be a damage-limitation
exercise and is meant to alleviate the pressure on the whole
government.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that key members of the ruling Democrat Party
agreed in talks Monday that with public pressure intensifying
daily, the government would become more vulnerable if it failed to
act.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, analysts warned that the government might be heading
for a premature fall if it is unable to eradicate corruption
within the coalition.
</P>
<P>
The move against Rakkiat has been prompted by growing public
dissatisfaction, which has shown itself in a campaign by public
interest groups to invoke a constitutional provision to initiate
his ouster.
</P>
<P>
The groups are collecting 50,000 signatures of eligible voters
necessary for asking the Parliament to dismiss people holding
political posts.
</P>
<P>
Despite Rakkiat's resignation Tuesday, leaders of the groups
said they will continue collecting the signatures in a bid to show
the will of the public.
</P>
<P>
Chuan said he has not decided who will be Rakkiat's successor.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said Tuesday that Rakkiat's resignation may lead to a
reshuffle of the cabinet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
