<HEADLINE> HK Has 575,000 Internet Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Statistics from a market
research group have showed that there are 575,000 Internet users
in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) of China,
the South China Morning Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The typical Internet user in Hong Kong is young, affluent and
male, but spends little time shopping online. E-mail is the most
popular Internet application, used by 61 percent of users, the
local newspaper reported, citing a study by market research group
AC Nielsen.
</P>
<P>
Other popular uses of the Internet include general surfing (47
percent), product or service information search (41 percent),
online newspaper reading (34 percent), and program downloading (31
percent).
</P>
<P>
Most established regional retailers regard virtual stores as
another sales channel that could give them an edge over
competitors, Chia Hork-hwa, a senior consulting and marketing
specialist for Eastern Consulting Group was quoted by the Post as
saying.
</P>
<P>
However, Chia said that Internet shoppers might be less loyal
than those who shop at store-front businesses and that confidence
is a key issue in attracting online customers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
