<HEADLINE> New Railway in Hong Kong on Track </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The West Rail will improve
transport services for more than one million residents in Hong
Kong's Northwest New Territories by providing a swift, convenient,
safe and reliable link with urban Kowloon, a government official
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Announcing here the authorization of the construction of the
West Rail (Phase I) by the Executive Council, Secretary for
Transport Nicholas Ng said the West Rail is expected to be
completed in 2003.
</P>
<P>
He said the West Rail would provide easy access for urban
residents to the rapidly growing Northwest New Territories in just
a 30-minute trip.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the West Rail will create about
13,000 jobs in the next few years. Everything being equal,
priorities will be given to local workers "in accordance with
government policy."
</P>
<P>
In assuring the public that the environmental impact of the
railway would be kept to the minimum, Ng said it is important that
both the government and residents of affected areas should closely
monitor the performance of the contractors involved and the
government will "ensure that environmental problems are addressed
promptly and effectively." 
</P>
</TEXT>
