<HEADLINE> Chinese Language Used in Predial Papers in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- In addition to Portuguese,
Chinese has become another language used in predial papers,
bringing remarkable convenience to the majority of Macao residents
who cannot read Portuguese.
</P>
<P>
The Predial Registration Bureau of Macao Monday demonstrated a
new bilingual computer program for predial registration.
</P>
<P>
The use of Chinese shows the equal position of the two official
languages and helps raise the transparency of administrative
affairs, said Jorge N. Silveira, secretary for justice affairs of
the Macao government.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese has been the only language in many government
papers, though Portuguese people constitute a tiny part of Macao's
population.
</P>
<P>
According to the secretary, Chinese will be gradually used
together with Portuguese in commercial, automobile and airplane
papers and other kinds of civil certificates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
