<HEADLINE> Share Prices Extend Gains on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices extended its
gains on heavy buying on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as the
benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 24.45 points to close
at 902.28 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover shot up to 640.09 million units worth 274.58
million Singapore dollars (159.27 million U.S. dollars). Advancers
led decliners by 290 to 103 with 194 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBF Cap was the most active stock of the day as it had a volume
of 20.49 million stocks traded. It was followed by Renong that had
20.30 million units done. MBF was next with 17.14 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 was the top gainer of the day as it climbed up 60
cents to close at 18.00 Singapore dollars. Tasek moved up 42 cents
to finish at 1.30 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem inched up 35 cents
to end 6.10 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Rothmans 200 was the biggest loser of the day
as it lost over 30 cents to close at 5.95 Singapore dollars.
Genting slid 30 cents to finish at 2.40 Singapore dollars. Seaview
shed off 28 cents to end at 3.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was encouraged by the expectation that
industrialized countries may be able to pull Asia out of its
doldrums.
</P>
<P>
They also said funds earmarked for Southeast Asia are flowing
into Singapore given the dearth of viable markets in which to
invest. 
</P>
