<HEADLINE> Fans Ready to Fight Sky Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Manchester United fans'
campaign against the BSkyB takeover will hit new heights on
Tuesday evening with a protest rally in the city.
</P>
<P>
The Independent Manchester United Supporters' Association
(IMUSA)is hoping fans will turn out in their thousands to show
their opposition to the proposed 623.4 million pounds deal.
</P>
<P>
IMUSA's campaign received a huge boost when rock star Roger
Taylor gave 10,000 pounds towards the costs of the rally at the
Bridgewater Hall.
</P>
<P>
Now IMUSA want others to follow Taylor's lead and donate money
and office facilities.
</P>
<P>
IMUSA chairman Andy Walsh said: "We will be making an appeal
tonight for more resources.
</P>
<P>
"Roger Taylor's generosity has kicked off the campaign but we
badly need more resources, such as office space, as well as
financial resources."
</P>
<P>
Walsh claimed that IMUSA would canvas opinion at the meeting
to devise the next steps in its battle to beat the takeover.
</P>
<P>
"Tonight will be an opportunity for United fans to decide the
strategy of our campaign," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We've shown in the last seven days that football fans can
make a difference if they band together.
</P>
<P>
"What we need now is for people to come and join us in this
campaign," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
