<HEADLINE> Computer Exhibition Opens In Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of computer,
telecommunications and office automation equipment was inaugurated
today in Guangzhou city, capital of southern China's Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth such exhibition, which will last
four days and has attracted 130 brand manufacturerers and
dealers, such as the Hewlett-Packard, the Philips and the Legend.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition covers an area of 5,000 sq.meters, with over 200
stalls.
</P>
<P>
In addition to trade talks, briefings and seminars on new
products will be held, during the exhibition.  
