roving exhibition here Tuesday to promote the Basic Law among the
civil servants of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR).
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the exhibition at Wanchai
Tower, Sandra Lee, acting secretary for the civil service, said
that the exhibition is one of the major activities of the
government to promote the Basic Law among the civil servants.
</P>
<P>
She said that it is very important for the civil servants to
learn the Basic Law. To learn the Basic Law is also a concrete
step for the civil servants to "understand one country and realize
two systems", Lee added.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Civil Service Bureau has done much in
enhancing the understanding of the Basic Law among the civil
servants.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,076 civil servants had attended training courses
and seminars on the Basic Law by the end of August and a large
number of books, pamphlets and video tapes had been distributed to
the civil servants to help them learn the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
