<HEADLINE> Commodities Fair Turnover Hits 7.38 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAOJI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The turnover at the 10th West
China Commodities Fair, which closed today in this commercial city
in northwest China's Shaanxi Province, totaled 7.38 billion yuan
(about 890 million US dollars), according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Of this amount, 5.13 billion yuan was between domestic dealers,
a record number for the event.
</P>
<P>
The five-day fair, co-sponsored by 11 prefectures and cities in
the provinces of Shaanxi, Gansu and Sichuan, and the Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region in cooperation with five railway sub-bureaus,
was attended by more than 20,000 business people from both at home
and abroad.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, a total of 16 overseas-funded projects were
signed, with overseas funds valued at 97.6 million US dollars in
the aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Official figures indicate that the commodity turnover for the
last 10 fairs has reached 43.8 billion yuan altogether.
</P>
<P>
