<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build Large American Grape Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's annual imports of popular Red Globe grapes stand at 723
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for the province, located along the ancient Silk
Road, to spend 800 million yuan (about 96.4 million US dollars)
over the next six-odd years to established the production base.
</P>
<P>
The Red Globe variety, which was introduced to China in the
mid-1980s, offers greater preservation qualities and ease in
transportation than most varieties of Chinese grapes.
</P>
<P>
China currently grows grapes on 166,660 ha, including 600 ha
dedicated to the production of the Red Globe variety.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi, one of the nation's major fruit production bases,
ranks closely behind the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Regions in
terms of ideal conditions for grape production.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that soil conditions, extended periods of
sunshine and mild temperatures will enable Shaanxi to produce
over 15,000 kg of Red Globe grapes per hectare.  
</P>
</TEXT>
