<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Population Estimated at 6.687 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The estimated mid-1998
population of Hong Kong was 6,687,200, according to figures
released by the Census and Statistics Department of Hong Kong here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A government announcement said there was an increase of 185,100
persons as compared with the figure of mid-1997, representing a
growth rate of 2.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The balance of arrivals and departures showed a net inflow of
some 161,800 persons from mid-1997 to mid-1998, constituting 87
percent of the population growth.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, there were 55,300 births and 32,000
deaths in Hong Kong. The natural increase amounted to 23,300,
accounting for 13 percent of the population growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
