<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eurasian Optical Cable to Benefit Macao Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Macao people will have closer
ties with the rest of the world and enjoy better multimedia
services when a Eurasian optical cable is put into use early next
year, according to sources at the Macao Telecommunications Company
 (CTM).
</P>
<P>
The cable will be 36,000 kilometers long and string together 33
countries and regions in Asia, Europe and Africa. A total of 92
telecommunications companies have participated in the project
which involves an investment of 2.04 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The laying of the cable started in June this year and is
expected to be completed by the end of March next year. Work to
lay the Macao stretch of the cable began in mid-August and CTM
will invest 38 million U.S. dollars in the project.
</P>
<P>
At present, international telecommunications services in Macao
are provided by means of satellite, microwave radio and land
optical cable via Zhuhai City of China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
