<HEADLINE> Camacho Confirmed New Coach of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Spanish Football
Federation on Tuesday confirmed their choice of Jose Antonio
Camacho as new national coach to succeed Javier Clemente after
accepting his demand to pick his own backroom staff.
</P>
<P>
Camacho said Monday that he would accept the new post only if
he were allowed a free rein to choose his own staff.
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old, who had previously coached Espanyol and Real
Madrid, succeeded Javier Clemente who resigned last week after a
humiliating loss in Euro 2000 qualifier opener in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Camacho is now set to sign a contract worth 80 million pesetas
(566,000 dollars) a season.
</P>
<P>
Camacho resigned as Real Madrid's coach as his side were
preparing for the defence of the European Cup following a
contractual disagreement. 
</P>
