<HEADLINE> Israeli Population at 5.98 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Israeli population was
registered at 5.987 million at the beginning of September, 8.4
times the figure 50 years ago when the country was established,
official statistics showed Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Jews constitute an absolute majority of 79.4 percent, Muslims
14.8 percent, Christians 2.1 percent, Druze 1.6 percent and people
with no religious category 2.1 percent, according to the latest
report from the Central Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The population has increased by 29.4 percent since early
1990s, when the mass influx of immigrants from the former Soviet
Union began.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics showed that nearly 170,000 Jewishes are
living in 144 settlements in the West Bank and Gaza Strip, a 3.3
percent increase from the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The report also showed that Israel now ranks 95th among 227
countries in terms of population, compared with the 137th place 50
years ago when there were far fewer countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
