<HEADLINE> Zambian Central Bank Invests $1.5M on Clearing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Bank of Zambia is investing three
billion Kwacha or 1.5 million U.S. Dollars in establishing an
Electronic Clearing House (ECH) to ease banking transactions in the
country's banking sector, Times of Zambia said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Chisha Mwanakatwe, the central bank's assistant
director, as saying that the ECH was expected to be operational
early next year.
</P>
<P>
He said the major gain would include reading of cheques
electronically and a subsequent decrease in the incidence of fraud and
criminality in the banking sector.
</P>
<P>
The house would also lower the processing error rates and
make it easier to handle large volumes of financial transactions,
according to Mwanakatwe.
</P>
<P>
He said, notwithstanding the developments in the country's banking
sector, the central bank had recognized the fact that further
innovations could still be instituted in order to streamline the
payment system.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the establishment of an clearing house, plans to build a
central depository which would be created in order to support the
financial sector so as to broaden the capital markets were also
underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
