<HEADLINE> French Prime Minister to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin will pay an official visit to China from September 24 to 26
at the invitation of Chinese Premier Zhu rongji.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu
Bangzao at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that China and France are both permanent
members of the United Nations Security Council and strengthing
consultations and cooperation between the two countries is
conducive to the interest of both and to world peace, stability
and development.
</P>
<P>
Sino-French relations have maintained good momentum and the
exchange of visits between the leaders and bilateral contacts in
the areas of economics and trade, science and technology, and
cultural fields have increased, with both sides having achieved
good results in friendly and mutually beneficial cooperation, Zhu
said.
</P>
<P>
China and France signed a Joint Communique on building an
all-round partnership for the 21st century when President Hirac
paid a state visit to China in May last year, and Premier Zhu
Rongji and Chairman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) National Committee Li Ruihuan visited France in
last April and May, he noted.
</P>
<P>
"We have always held that the exchange of high-level visits is
vital in promoting Sino-French relations. And Rospin's forthcoming
visit, a continuation of those visits, is an important event in
Sino-French relations this year," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He continued that during the visit, Jospin and Chinese leaders
are expected to have in-depth exchange of views on a wide range of
issues including bilateral and international issues.
</P>
<P>
The visit will promote further development of the Sino-French
partnership, Zhu said. 
</P>
