<HEADLINE> Four Japanese Expelled for Illegal Border-Crossing Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Four Japanese criminal
suspects who attempted to help two Chinese cross the border
illegally were put on trial in Shanghai and expelled from
China yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The two Japanese, Funahashi Shiyo and Jitsukawa Daisuke, were
sentenced to three years in prison and fined 50,000 yuan (about
6,200 U.S. dollars), and four years in prison and fined 40,000
yuan, respectively. The Shanghai No.1 intermidate people's court
passed the sentences on the grounds that the two organized illegal
border-crossing activities.
</P>
<P>
Ishiyama Yoshinayi and Teyada Shimpei, the other two Japanese,
were each sentenced to six months in prison and fined 30,000
yuan. They were charged with selling illegal exit and entry
documents.
</P>
<P>
All four criminal suspects were expelled from China after the
sentencing. 
</P>
