<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets Socialist International President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- All countries and various
political forces, their leaders in particular, should strengthen
dialogue and cooperation and explore ways to bring a peaceful yet
prosperous world into the 21st century, Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
And this should be done in line with the principle of seeking
common ground while preserving differences, as at the turn of the
century mankind is faced with various kinds of new problems
related to peace and development, said Jiang, also General
Secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks here this morning at a meeting with
Pierre Mauroy, president of the Socialist International and former
prime minister of France.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to the Socialist International delegation
headed by Mauroy, Jiang said that in recent years the
international situation has seen drastic changes, with accelerated
multi-polarization and economic globalization, and international
relations undergoing fundamental readjustments and changes.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Political parties with different ideologies should
advocate the practice of mutual respect, equal dialogue, increased
understanding and stronger cooperation."
</P>
<P>
The CPC and the Socialist International and its member parties
can surpass their ideological differences and undertake exchanges
and cooperation, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that since the reform and open-up in 1978, the CPC has
put forward four new guiding principles for party-to-party
relations: independence and self-reliance, equality, mutual
respect and non-interference into each other's internal affairs,
and this has been well received by various political parties
around the world.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the CPC will strengthen contacts and expand
cooperation with the Socialist International on the basis of these
principles in an effort to promote world peace, stability and
development.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the guests on China's reform and open-up and
the recent flood control efforts.
</P>
<P>
Mauroy thanked the CPC for inviting his delegation to visit
China and said he was glad to visit China after a lapse of 13
years and in his new capacity as president.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Socialist International treasures its ties
with the CPC and hopes to continue bilateral dialogue and
cooperation in various forms in a bid to explore ways to solve
major world problems and develop dialogue and cooperation in the
next century.
</P>
<P>
The Socialist International delegation arrived here Sunday as
guests of the CPC, and Dai Bingguo, head of the International
Department of the CPC Central Committee, has held working talks
with them.  
</P>
