<HEADLINE> Sino-British Joint Liaison Group Meets in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-British Joint
Liaison Group (JLG) began its 43rd meeting here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The JLG, which meets alternately in Beijing, London and
Hong Kong, is meeting for the first time in Hong Kong after it
returned to China on July 1 last year.
</P>
<P>
At the start of the two-day meeting, Senior Chinese
Representative Wang Guisheng extended a warm welcome to the
British delegation led by Senior Representative Ambassador Alan
Paul.
</P>
<P>
