<HEADLINE> Israeli Local Authority Workers Launch Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Most of Israel's municipal
departments, hospitals and kindergartens were closed Tuesday as
employees of local authorities began a strike demanding higher
wages.
</P>
<P>
The industrial action involved some 100,000 employees across
the country.
</P>
<P>
The walkout came as talks between the Trade Union of Local
Authorities and the Finance Ministry broke down last night as the
treasury rejected a 30 percent salary rise required by the union.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Finance Ministry said that they would agree
to a wage increase of no more than 27 percent.
</P>
<P>
Leon Morozovsky, general secretary of the union, said that they
will return to work only after their demands are met.
</P>
<P>
"There is no way that I will allow workers to receive less than
a 30 percent increase," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
