<HEADLINE> Chi Haotian Meets President of US National Defense University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councillor and
Defense Minister Chi Haotian met here today with Richard Chilcoat,
president of the US National Defense University, and his party.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Chilcoat is the fifth sitting president of US
National Defense University who visited China, Chi said that the
National Defense University of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) and the US National Defense University enjoy a close
relationship.
</P>
<P>
He added that the exchange of visits between the leaders of the
two national defense universities has made important contributions
to the growth of the friendly relations between the two armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
Chilcoat echoed with Chi that the exchange between the two
universities of national defense is important to the development
of US-China ties.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
briefed the US visitors on China's flood control campaign and the
country's rebuilding effort in the flood-hit areas.
</P>
<P>
The flood control campaign has been a test of China's
comprehensive national strength as well as an exercise and test of
the PLA, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
Chilcoat and his party are visiting China at the invitation of
Xing Shizhong, president of China's National Defense University.
</P>
