<HEADLINE> Thailand Eyes High-Speed Telecommunications Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Telephone Organization of
Thailand (TOT) plans to establish a high-speed fiber-optic
telecommunications network to keep up with the world's pace of
information technology development.
</P>
<P>
A source of the organization said Tuesday that the TOT board
met earlier Tuesday to discuss the future of the ambitious
project.
</P>
<P>
Board Chairman Mechai Viravaidya asked the board for the
approval of an additional 3.4 billion baht (85 million U.S.
dollars) for the project because of the baht's depreciation.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10.4 billion baht (260 million dollars) has already
been approved, the source said.
</P>
<P>
However, the source predicted that the Transport and
Communications Ministry may reject the request until more details
are given to back the project, which will use technology known as
synchronous digital hierarchy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
