<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Hits Northeastern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A fairly strong earthquake
measuring 5.1 on the open-ended Richter scale jolted Miyagi and
Yamagata prefectures in northeast Japan Tuesday afternoon, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage from
the quake, which occurred at 4:24 p.m. local time (0724 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was about 10 kilometers underground
in the southern Miyagi Prefecture, the agency added. 
</P>
