<HEADLINE> Canada, Australia Win Cycling Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Eric Wohlberg
and Australian Anna Wilsonus picked up men's and women's cycling
time trial golds respectively at the Commonwealth Games on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wohlberg took the men's 42-kilometer time trial with a time of
53 minutes and 05 seconds after Australian Stuart O'Grady crashed
on a curve and lost more than two minutes.
</P>
<P>
O'Grady skidded into a barrier about two-thirds of the way
through the race, got up, changed bicycles and set off again with
blood running down his left arm and leg.
</P>
<P>
He clocked in 53 minutes, 30 seconds for a silver medal. South
African David George took the bronze in 53:56.
</P>
<P>
Another Australian Anna Wilsonus, however, grabbed the women's
28-kilometer time trial in 37:34, one minute ahead of Canada's
Linda Jackson
</P>
<P>
Jackson was five seconds ahead of Australian Kathy Watt, who
had been set back 29 seconds at the start by a broken strap on
her shoe. Watt's fiance, Carey Hall, scrambled to apply masking
tape to keep her foot from slipping.  
</P>
</TEXT>
