<HEADLINE> 5 Tamil Rebels, 3 Govt Soldiers Killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- At Least five Tamil rebels
and three soldiers were killed Monday in fierce fighting in the
north and east of Sri Lanka between the rebels and government
troops, a military spokesman here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops on patrol were
attacked by a group of terrorists around 12:45 p.m. Monday at
Vanthaharamoolai in Batticaloa district in the east of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated and reinforcements were sent to the
location from nearby detachments.
</P>
<P>
Upon the arrival of the reinforcements, terrorists fled the
area with their casualties, Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
On a subsequent search in the area, troops recovered one rebel
dead body. Three government soldiers were killed and five soldiers
were injured during the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
In another incident around 10:15 a.m. Monday at Rawattamunai in
the same district, troops observed terrorist movement and engaged
them with small arms and mortars.
</P>
<P>
The troops confirmed two rebels were killed due to the fire.
</P>
<P>
On the same day around 4:00 p.m. at Periya Paranthankulam in
Kilinochchi district in the north of the country, government
troops observed a rebel movement ahead of the defenses and engaged
them with small arms, killing at least two rebels.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a war for a separate state in
the north and east of the island country since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
