<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CAST To Celebrate 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The China Association for
Science and Technology (CAST), the largest scientific organization
in the world with a membership of 4.3 million, will celebrate its
40th anniversary next week.
</P>
<P>
A series of academic meetings and science expositions will be
held in Beijing and other major cities beginning this weekend and
lasting until December, according to a CAST official.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 600 scientists and technologists, including 30
academicians from the Chinese Academy of Sciences and the Chinese
Academy of Engineering, will come out of their laboratories to
share their scientific knowledge with average citizens on the
streets on Sept. 19.
</P>
<P>
A total of 32 of China's key laboratories in research
institutes and universities will be opened to citizens and
students during this period.
</P>
<P>
Founded in September 1958, CAST's aim is to raise the
scientific and cultural level of the entire nation. CAST also
organizes and supports its members in academic exchanges and in
the compilation and publication of academic studies. It has served
as a link between the government and the nation's scientists and
technologists.
</P>
<P>
After four decades of development, CAST now has 165 national
scientific societies and over 4.3 million members, many of whom
have made great contributions to China's scientific and economic
development, said Zhang Yutai, vice president of CAST.
</P>
<P>
An anniversary ceremony will be held on September 23, and a
series of academic meetings during September 22-24 are expected to
draw 1,600 scientists from both home and abroad, according to
Zhang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
