beginning of September, meaning one in every 1,000 people in the
world is an Israeli citizen, according to latest official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Jews constitute 79.4 percent of the population, while Muslims
account for 14.8 percent, Christians 2.1 percent and Druze 1.6
percent. 
