<DOCNO> XIE19980915.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SADC Underlines Information Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GRAND BAIE, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Southern
African Development Community (SADC) were urged early Tuesday
morning to deal with the challenge and opportunities of
information technology to draw advantage from the process of
globalization.
</P>
<P>
"As we pursue our vision of development through regional
integration, and the path of sustained growth which will enable
us to eradicate poverty, diseases and unemployment, we must act
expeditiously, lest the world leaves us behind," said South
African President Nelson Mandela, Chairman of SADC, at the
closing ceremony of the SADC summit.
</P>
<P>
A communique, issued at the end of the summit, said that it
is satisfied that member states have continued to implement
sound economic policies that augur well for long-term sustainable
development. It also praised the positive annual growth rates of
the member states in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
It said that the 1997 average gross domestic product
growth rate stood at 2.2 percent while budget deficits and
inflation rates decreased dramatically to six percent and 10
percent respectively during the same period.
</P>
<P>
The communique appealed to both local and foreign investors to
fully take advantage of the changing economic situation to
further increase intra-regional trade beyond the current 20
percent of total SADC trade.
</P>
<P>
The summit undertook to enhance efforts to coordinate and
rationalize programs of economic reconstruction, to give more
impetus to the region's emerging market of over 185 million
people with a combined GDP of more that 160 billion U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
There was concern over the unfavorable weather conditions
which prevailed during the 1997/1998 cropping season
characterized by erratic and below normal rainfall in some
countries and excessive rains in others, resulting in a projected
overall cereal deficit of 510,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The summit undertook to ensure, through relevant institutions
and implementation of appropriate contingency plans, to address
cereal deficts, particularly in wheat, sorghum and millet, to
avoid suffering by vulnerable groups.
</P>
<P>
During the SADC meeting from September 7 to 14, a new
protocol on tourism was signed which aims to ensure balanced and
complemetary development of the tourism industry in the region
through collective efforts.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state and government of the 14-member regional
grouping expressed satisfaction at the progress being made in the
implementation of the African Economic Community, following the
signing of the Protocol on the relations between the African
Economic Community and other regional economic communities on
February 25 of this year in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
They reaffirmed their decision of 1995, that all the
activities and policies of SADC should be carried out in the
context of achieveing the objectives of teh African Economic
Community.
</P>
<P>
The summit committed SADC as a building bloc, to play a
catalytic and strategic role in the process of establishing the
Community.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the communique noted that Nelson Mandela would
retire from office early next year before SADC's next meeting,
which has been scheduled to be held in Maputo, Mozambique next
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
