<HEADLINE> Two Tamil Rebels Surrender to Sri Lankan Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Two rebels of the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) Monday surrendered to Sri Lankan
government troops at Batticaloa in Eastern province, according to
military sources here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said they confessed that they joined the LTTE about
a year ago on the promise that they could visit their parents
every three months, but ever since they were not allowed to visit
home in Vanni.
</P>
<P>
They had not got even two meals a day for the past three
months, said the sources, adding that according to the two rebels,
in LTTE, there are many others who want to defect but they have
not done so due to fear of their leaders.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a civil war against the Sri
Lankan government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and
east of the island country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
