<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Meets Former Peruvian President of Council of Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), met with Edgardo Mercado Jarrin, former
president of the Council of Ministers of Peru, here today.
</P>
<P>
Li voiced his appreciation of the efforts made by Mercado in
promoting Sino-Peruvian relations over the past years.
</P>
<P>
Peru is a country of major influence in Latin America and China
has scored great progress since it adopted the reform and open
policy, Li said, adding that the further enhancement of the
cooperative relations between the two countries would enjoy a
broad prospect.
</P>
<P>
Li told Mercado that China has won a "great victory" in flood
control. Although there are still difficulties following the
torrential floods, China has various favorable conditions and is
confident of accomplishing the task of rebuilding the flood-hit
areas and the country's economic and social development, Li stated.
</P>
<P>
Mercado spoke highly of China's enormous achievements in its
reform, opening to the outside world and economic construction. He
also voiced his admiration of the heroism of the Chinese people
demonstrated in their struggle against floods.
</P>
<P>
He told Li that Peru hopes to advance its friendly and
cooperative ties with China.
</P>
<P>
Mercado and his party are visiting China at the invitation of
the Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs. 
</P>
