<HEADLINE> China, Peru Agree on Closer Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice Premier Wu
Bangguo and Peruvian Prime Minister Alberto Pandolfi discussed
ways to expand economic cooperation between the two countries here
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Wu said China and Peru have become partners of mutual trust in
the past 27 years since the establishment of their diplomatic
relations, especially during the office of President Alberto
Fujimori.
</P>
<P>
Their friendly cooperation has achieved considerable progress
in various fields, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Wu said both China and Peru are developing countries and
members of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation forum, with
similar historical background and common challenges.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to make joint efforts with Peru to forge a
long-term stable friendship and develop overall cooperation
oriented to the 21st century, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed ways to strengthen their economic and
trade ties and saw great potentials in their mutually beneficial
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the two countries should expand areas for
cooperation and increase contacts between their business circles.
</P>
<P>
Pandolfi said the development of bilateral relations offered a
rare opportunity for the economic and trade cooperation between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He added the two governments should make further efforts to
strengthen the bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese official expressed gratitude for Lima's support to
the Chinese investments in Peru and hopes for continuing support.
</P>
<P>
Wu also expressed appreciation for Lima's long-standing
one-China policy.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed agreements on shipping and economic
technology cooperation after the meeting. 
</P>
