<HEADLINE> Shipment to Asia Through Panama Canal Decreases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA City, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Shipments to Asia via the
Panama Canal have been reduced by 10.4 percent to 53.8 million metric
tons in the first 11 months of the 1998 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
According to a report published here on Monday by the Panama
Canal Commission, from October 1997 to August 1998, the deadweight
tonnage that went to Japan was about 50 percent of the total
shipment to Asia, which decreased 2.6 percent or 26.5 million
metric tons in that period.
</P>
<P>
The reduction is a result of the Asian financial crisis, the
report said. 
</P>
