<HEADLINE> Honduran in Plane's Wheel Well Survives Hours-Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A Honduran man who hid
inside the landing gear of an Iberia Airlines jet survived a
two-hour flight from his country to the United States Monday, the
Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The man was discovered by mechanics during a check over the
aircraft, Carmen Lopez-Calleja, spokeswoman for the Spanish
airline, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The plane departed from San Pedro Sula, Honduras, and arrived
at Miami International Airport after a two-hour flight. The DC-9,
which was carrying 15 passengers, plus crew, flew as high as
10,000 meters and the temperatures reached below zero while there
was no oxygen.
</P>
<P>
However, the man, identified as 23-year-old Emilio Dominguez,
appeared to be in good condition, with no visible signs of trauma,
Lopez-Calleja said. Paramedics checked him over before he was
turned over to immigration authorities.
</P>
<P>
Dominguez told immigration officials he had been hiding in the
aircraft's back wheel well since Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The airline was to return him to Honduras on the next flight
Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
