<HEADLINE> Ecuador Devalues Currency by 15 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador devalued its currency
by 15 percent on Monday, and traded by as much as 6,700 sucres to
the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The sucre, which was devalued by 7.5 percent in March, was at
5,625 sucres to the dollar on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Central Bank chairman Luis Jacome said the measure was taken in
a bid to fight inflation which had totaled 24 percent from January
to August.
</P>
<P>
Jacome told a news conference that, under the terms of the
devaluation, the sucre's trading band against the dollar will be
raised to 5,833-6,740. 
</P>
