<HEADLINE> Australia Sweeps all-round Gymnastics Medals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Australian gymnasts
swept all three medals in the women's all-round competition and
won a gold and bronze in the men's competition at the Commonweal
the Games here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Russian-born Andrei Kravtsov overcame a shoulder injury and a
persistent challenge by England's Andrew Atherton to win the
men's individual gold while Brennon Dowrick won the bronze.
</P>
<P>
In the women's events, Zeena McLaughlin took the gold with
37.917 points, Allana Slater took the silver with 37.324 and
Trudy McIntosh the bronze with 36.636.
</P>
<P>
Kravtsov, a 27-year-old Russian who moved to Australia almost
six years ago, finished with 54.675 while Atherton got the silver
with 54.025 points in what was largely a two-man race.
</P>
<P>
Dowrick, trailing in fifth place after the fifth rotation,
scored a 9.250 on the pommel horse in the sixth and final
routine, jumping to a bronze-medal finish with 52.500.
</P>
<P>
In the women's action, while McLaughlin was leading the field
from the beginning, the clutch performer turned out to be the
14-year-old McIntosh, who stood fifth after the first rotation.
She went into the final rotation needing 8.680 or more to keep
her third position from being snatched by Holly Murdoch of
Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
But McIntosh's last event was the vault, her favorite
exercise, which earned her 9.312 points and helped seal the
win.  
</P>
</TEXT>
