<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Fu Sets Sights on World University Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, China, Spetember 15 (Xinhua) -- Fu Mingxia, winner of
three Olympic diving gold medals, said on Tuesday that she aims
to take part in the World University Games in 1999 and 2001
instead of Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Fu, who became a students at the pretigious Qinghua
University after the Atlanta Olympic Games, resumed training last
July.
</P>
<P>
"I just returned to the pool two months ago." said Fu, who
won her first gold at the Barcelona Games in 1992 at age 14 and
two more at Atlanta in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The former diving queen, who came here to watch the National
Diving Championships starting on Monday, said that she is willing
to compete in the World University Games as a representative of
Qinghua.
</P>
<P>
"I'm a students of Qinghua University. I have the respons
ibility to dive for her," the 20-year-old said. "So far, I have
not thought about the Sydney Olympic Games."
</P>
<P>
The Qinghua University has a well-known diving team under the
charge of former national coach Yu Fen, who coached Fu to win the
Olympic champion.
</P>
<P>
But it's an open secret that Yu and Fu had a quarrel about
prize money and it was reported that the two have not been on
very good terms since.
</P>
<P>
Yu didn't lead her new divers to compete in the national
championships, but she was believed to shine again in
international arena in the near future.
</P>
<P>
"Yu has got some new divers from around the coutry this
semester. She has a lot to do helping them make adjustments,"
said Gao Bin, head of the diving team of Qinghua University. "But
I'm sure she will appear in major tournaments next year."
</P>
