<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Destroys Tamil Rebels' Boats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan navy Monday
destroyed five boats of Tamil rebel "Sea Tigers" off the coast of
Mullaitivu in Northern Province and killed at least 10 rebels,
reports reaching here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The navy detected eight Sea Tiger boats moving from Mullaitivu
towards Trincomalee and during an ensuing one-hour battle,
destroyed five of them, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted Navy sources as saying that all the crew in
the five boats were presumed to have been killed. The Navy
estimated there were at least 10 rebels aboard the five boats.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a war against the Sri Lankan
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the island country. 
