<HEADLINE> Hebei Province Sets to Achieve 11 Percent Annual Growth Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Increased investments in
fixed assets enabled North China's Hebei Province to record 9.6
percent growth in GDP for the first half of this year compared to
the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Increased investments are expected to boost local economic
growth for the year to 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
Fixed asset investments for the year are expected to rise 19
percent on the 1997 level to 170 billion yuan. The bulk of
investments will go to basic industries, infrastructure,
technological upgrades, the high technology sector, residential
housing construction, power grids in rural areas, state grain
reserves and afforestation.
</P>
<P>
Local state-owned businesses and various other economic
entities invested close to 28.6 billion yuan in fixed assets
during the period, up 11.4 percent from the same period last year,
</P>
<P>
Investments in local agriculture grew by 21 percent on the 1997
period, with 23 percent growth for the power industry, 30
percent for the transportation and telecommunications
sectors, 26 percent for technological upgrades and a dramatic 40
percent rise for urban infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
The province ranked 5th in the nation with an 11.3 percent jump
in industrial output value during the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The summer grain output hit 12.55 million tons, the second
largest seasonal harvest in history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
