<HEADLINE> Giant Panda Cub Born In Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A male giant panda was
recently born in southwest China's Chongqing Municipality thanks
to joint efforts of the Chongqing and Shanghai zoos
</P>
<P>
The cub, which weighed 2,800 grams at birth, is the offspring
of Xinxing from the Chongqing Zoo and Chuanchuan from the Shanghai
Zoo.
</P>
<P>
The two pandas have bred in February and March each year, and
have given birth to seven cubs. Four cubs have survived.
</P>
<P>
Xinxing, the mother, feeds and cares for the cub. Chuanchuan
lives in the Shanghai Zoo and an agreement reached between the two
sides calls for the cub to be moved to Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
