<HEADLINE> Ningxia Pushes up Animal Husbandry Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia
Hui Autonomous Region has taken full advantage of its natural
resources and experience over the past two decades to establish
animal husbandry as a pillar industry.
</P>
<P>
An official with the regional Animal Husbandry Bureau reported
that the total 1997 output value for the industry hit two billion
yuan, accounting for 32.5 percent of the region's total
agricultural output.
</P>
<P>
Figures show the output for meat hit 140,000 tons, with outputs
for eggs hitting 48,000 tons and milk 210,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia has over 2.3 million hectares of grassland dedicated to
animal husbandry. The region's program to replant and improve over
200,000 hectares of grassland in recent years has resulted in a
considerable rise in grass production.
</P>
<P>
The region has spent over 100 million yuan to improve some
50-odd animal husbandry infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Fine technology has played an important role in the
process. Ningxia has applied over 80 scientific achievements
related to animal husbandry in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of special breeds of livestock has also
contributed to the development of the local animal husbandry. Some
1,200 artificial breeding centers have introduced over 14 species
of animals and have recorded a total output value over 500 million
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
