<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Olympic 100 meters champion
Donovan Bailey of Canada still has obstacles to overcome before a
complete recovery from his achilles tendon operation, his doctor
revealed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from Montreal, the 30-year-old tore his
achilles tendon on Wednesday while playing basketball with
friends and had a successful operation on Friday.
</P>
