<HEADLINE> Guangdong Businesses Join Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of
Guangdong business people are striking deals via the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The five-star White Swan Hotel took the lead two years ago when
it started booking reservations via the Internet. Over 34,000
local residents and business people in Guangzhou, the provincial
capital, have established Internet links.
</P>
<P>
Companies point to the convenience and efficiency that Internet
offers compared to traditional practices such as participating in
trade fairs and erecting billboards.
</P>
<P>
A vegetable company in Dongguan city recently joined the
Internet and within a short period received orders from a chain
store in the United States and a company from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,000 firms in the Pearl River Delta city of Nanhai are
conducting business via computerized information net which the
local government established at a cost of over 100 million yuan
(12.05 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Jiuzhou Chemical Products Plant recently solicited funding
for an expansion project and received promising inquiries from a
number of foreign companies, including US-based Du Pont. 
</P>
