<HEADLINE> Ningbo Sets up Funds to Aid Poor Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The port city of Ningbo in
east China's Zhejiang Province has initiated a program to help
poor students continue with their education.
</P>
<P>
The city's labor union has earmarked a monthly subsidy of 300
yuan (about 37 U.S. dollars) for every poverty-stricken family who
has had a child in primary or high schools since last autumn. More
than 200 families have received the subsidy, and 400 families have
developed mutual-help relations.
</P>
<P>
The city's education foundation has establish a special fund to
help children living in extreme poverty, and more than 230
students will each receive 3,000 yuan in assistance from the fund.
</P>
<P>
A charity education project also has been launched by the city's
charity society which has raised 420,000 yuan for the city's
students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
