<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malta Submits Reapplication to Join EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Maltese Foreign Minister Guido
de Marco Monday submitted Malta's reapplication for membership in
the European Union to Austrian Foreign Minister Wolfgang
Schuessel, who currently heads the EU Commission of Foreign
Ministers.
</P>
<P>
Malta's first application, made in July 1990, was withdrawn by
the Labor government in October 1996. After the Nationalist Party
won the elections eight days ago, Prime Minister Edward
Fenech Adami immediately announced the resumption of the
application.
</P>
<P>
De Marco told a press conference here that his country had for
years adhered to a policy of moving closer to the EU and the
two-year suspension of the application would not interfere with
its continuing the policy.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the hope for Malta to be one of EU's first new
members.
</P>
<P>
However, Malta maintains its neutral status and is not
considering membership in the North Atlantic Treaty Organization,
De Marco said during the question session.
</P>
<P>
Also at the press conference, the Austrian foreign minister
expressed EU's welcome to Malta's application but added that
everything should be in accordance with rules and regulations
while no timetable could be fixed at present. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
