<HEADLINE> Australia Taks Five Gymnastic Medals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Australia took five of
the six medals for gymnastics at the Commonwealth Games including
three in the women's all-round individual and two from the three
men's medals on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Zeena McLaughlin, Allana Slater and Trudy McIntosh became
Australia's first in 20 years to win all the medals in the
women's all-round individual. The last Commonwealth nation to
claim that credit was Canada in 1978.
</P>
<P>
In the men's section, Andrei Kravtsov overcame pain from a
nagging shoulder injury to win Australia's first gold in the
men's all-round individuals.
</P>
<P>
Brennon Dowrick was stopped from making it a clean sweep for
Australia, having to be content with the the bronze behind
England's Andrew Atherthon.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, the Australians won the women's team gold, after
England took the silver and Canada bronze and Australia have now
won three of the four gold medals for gymnastics so far.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday is a rest day for gymnastics but Wednesday will see
heavy action with as many as 10 gold medals at stake in the men
and women's individual artistic exercise events.  
</P>
</TEXT>
