<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Flood-Ravaged Areas Enjoy Stable Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Flood-ravaged areas in Hunan
Province and Chongqing Municipality continue to enjoy stable
prices for vegetables and other daily-use items.
</P>
<P>
Price hikes for vegetables in Hunan's Yueyang City, one of the
areas most affected by flooding around Dongting Lake, have
remained within the 10 percent range in spite of sustantial drops
in output due to the destruction of vegetable production bases
covering over 4,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts attribute the ample vegetable supply to
virtually intact railway and highway networks which have ensured a
constant flow of products from other provinces.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing, an area hit by an extended period of heavy rain and
landslides, has also enjoyed stable prices for vegetable and goods
of daily necessities, according to a survey of ten local districts
and counties.
</P>
<P>
The achievement has been attributed to the municipality's
timely efforts to distribute supplies to disaster-stricken areas
and to strict measure preventing market speculation in the wake of
the natural disaster. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
