<HEADLINE> Brazil's Steel Imports Increase by 46 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Although it is the world's
seventh largest producer of steel, Brazil's imports of steel
registered a 46 percent increase in the first half of this year,
compared to the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to data published by the Iron and Steel Industry
Institute, Brazil imported last year 790,000 metric tonns of
steel, a 109.5 percent growth compared to the 377,000 metric tonns
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's average annual production of steel is 25 million
metric tonns. 
</P>
