<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, September 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States, backing away from its initial
assessment, concluded Monday that the Democratic People's Republic
of Korea (DPRK) launched a satellite two weeks ago, but not a
missile.
</P>
<P>
"We have concluded that North Korea did attempt to orbit a very
small satellite," State Department spokesman James Rubin told
reporters. "We also have concluded the satellite failed to
achieve orbit," he added.
</P>
<P>
The August 31 rocket firing was first described by
U.S. officials as a multi-stage Taepo Dong-1 missile that has a
range of more than 1,930 km and has been viewed as threatening,
especially by Japan.
</P>
<P>
Until now, the United States has tended to ignore official DPRK
statement that the Aug. 31 launch involved a satellite, although
South Korea's foreign minister said in Washington last Friday that
based on talks with U.S. experts it appeared that a satellite
launch was most probable. (US-DPRK-Satellite)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Iraq demanded once again on Monday that the
Security Council of the United Nations initiate a serious
investigation of the United Nations Special Commission (UNSCOM) in
charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the Security Council, Iraq's Deputy Prime
Minister Tareq Aziz said initiating a probe may correct the
situation within UNSCOM and make it to be an impartial
international body.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has complained that UNSCOM is controlled by the United
States and it is the United States which decides on the
Commission's agenda and even on its working methods.
(Iraq-UNSCOM-Probe)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- The bodies of seven Iranians killed by Afghan Taliban
militia have been identified by the International Committee of the
Red Cross (ICRC), the Iranian official news agency IRNA reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
It said that an ICRC team has left Afghanistan for Tehran after
identifying the bodies with assistance from an Iranian technical
team.
</P>
<P>
The ICRC team was dispatched to Afghanistan to identify and
transfer the bodies of the Iranian diplomats and IRNA reporter
killed on August 8 in Mazari Sharif when the Taliban took over the
city.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Mohsen Aminzadeh on Monday
told a group of foreign diplomats that eight Iranian diplomats
and an IRNA correspondent were killed by the Taliban, a diplomat
source told Xinhua. (Iran-Diplomats-Identified)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
BC-NATO-Albania-Violence
hke -- NATO Concerned over Weekend Violence in Albania
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The secretary-general of the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) Monday expressed his
concern over the violence triggered by the murder of an opposition
politician in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Javier Solana called on all sides to show utmost restraint and
create conditions for the restoration of peace and stability in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Solana said that NATO was committed to promoting stability and
security in the Balkan country where the western military alliance
has been cooperating with the Albanian government through NATO's
Partnership for Peace programs.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, demonstrators shot their way into the office of
Socialist Prime Minister Fatos Nano and set the ground floor on
fire in protest against the murder of Azem Hajdari and his
bodyguard. (NATO-Albania-Violence) 
