</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980915.0320 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SADC Summit Ends with Condemnation of UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GRAND BAIE, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The two-day summit of
heads of states and government of the Southern African African
Community (SADC) ended here well after midnight with all members
condemning Angola's opposition UNITA.
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela, the current chairman
of the SADC, said in his closing speech that the regional
grouping condemned strongly the "flagrant non-compliance with the
major provisions of the Lusaka Protocol" in 1994 by the National
Union for Total Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The heads of the 14 SADC members concluded that "the behavior
of Jonas Savimbi, chairman of the former rebel UNITA movement, is
that of a war criminal" which thus "renders him objectively
incapable of leading his party onto the road to peace in Angola,"
said a SADC summit statement on Angola read by Kaire Mbuende,
executive secretary of the SADC.
</P>
<P>
The heads of the southern African countries expressed their
full support to the movement of renewal within UNITA launched by
its cadres and political leaders of that party, and recognize in
them sufficient competence to act as capable and valid
negotiators with the government of Angola in the search for a
just solution aimed at ending the peace process and strengthening
democracy in Angola, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the leaders appeal to the United Nations, the
troika of observers and the entire international community to
recognize the new leadership of UNITA, assist and encourage it to
cooperate fully with the Angolan government in accomplishing the
Lusaka peace accord.
</P>
<P>
The tireless efforts by the Angolan government in bringing
about peace in the country are also praised by the SADC heads.
</P>
<P>
They urged the international community to fully support the
government to facilitate the social integration of demobilized
soldiers and the involvement of all Angolan citizens.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the summit noted that it will be ensured that
decisions taken by the member states through the SADC, the
Organization of African Unity and the U.N. are complied with and
that international community would intensify pressure on UNITA to
demilitarize as required so that the people of Angola can start
rebuilding the country.
</P>
<P>
On the Lesotho issue, SADC is ready to continue its efforts to
facilitate an end of the problems that have arisen there
concerning the results of the elections.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state are confident that leaders of Lesotho will
find a satisfactory solution as the mediation initiative will be
taken by four SADC members consisting of Botswana, Mozambique,
Zimbabwe and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The sub-regional grouping also expressed its commitment to
giving all necessary support to the efforts to restore peace,
security and stability to the Democratic Republic of Congo on the
basis of the Victoria Falls and Pretoria initiatives, as the
start of a peaceful transition to democracy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
